    "text": "34-11 to 34-19 Astoria Boulevard, north side, between 34th and 35th Streets. The frame house is no. 34-11 and 15. These, as well as other buildings on the north side of the Boulevard, were later torn down for the construction of the Grand Central Parkway approach to the Triborough Bridge.\nView 2 shows the same group of buildings being torn down, seen from 35th Street.\n\nView 1: March 11, 1931\nView 2: September 20, 1934\n\nP. L. Sperr\n",
